  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a low heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and cook for 10-15 min until softened and caramelised</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1204.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1204.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1204.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1204.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1204.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks (reserve a few leaves for garnish)</p><p>Cut your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1204.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1204.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1204.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1204.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1204.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Drain and rinse your <strong>chickpeas</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1204.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1204.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1204.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1204.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1204.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your<strong> spinach</strong>, then add it to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the<strong> wilted spinach</strong> under <strong>cold running water </strong>until it’s cool</p><p>Once cool, squeeze as much water out of the spinach as you can, then roughly chop</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1204.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1204.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1204.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1204.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1204.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, increase the heat to medium, add your <strong>garam masala</strong> and <strong>ground</strong> <strong>turmeric</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>ginger</strong>, <strong>coriander </strong>and<strong> chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>with your <strong>tomato paste</strong> and cook for 1 min further</p><p>Add the <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock</strong>,<strong> halved cherry tomatoes </strong>and <strong>drained chickpeas </strong>and cook for 10 min or until the liquid has reduced to a thick sauce</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1204.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1204.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1204.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1204.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1204.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the sauce is thickening, add your <strong>garlic & coriander naan[s]</strong> to a <strong>toaster</strong> for 1-2 min or until warmed through</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Mini-naans-in-toaster-1674048127415-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Mini-naans-in-toaster-1674048127415-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Mini-naans-in-toaster-1674048127415-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Mini-naans-in-toaster-1674048127415-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Mini-naans-in-toaster-1674048127415-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>natural yoghurt</strong> and <strong>mint sauce</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>in a bowl – this is your<strong> mint raita</strong></p><p>Once the sauce has thickened, stir the <strong>chopped spinach</strong> through the chickpea curry – this is your<strong> chana masala</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1204.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1204.-step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1204.-step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1204.-step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1204.-step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>chana masala</strong> with the <strong>warmed</strong> <strong>naan[s]</strong> and<strong> mint raita</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>coriander leaves</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
